# =============================================================================
# Dependency manifest (requirements.in) for the midas py-analysis-base image.
#
# This is the human-edited, loose-constraint list of TOP-LEVEL packages baked
# into ghcr.io/dom-midas/py-analysis-base. It is the Python analog of the R
# image's manifest/DESCRIPTION Imports:.
#
# It is NOT what gets installed. It is compiled to a fully pinned, hash-locked
# requirements.txt (every transitive dep, version + sha256) with:
#
#   scripts/compile-py-requirements.sh
#
# which runs `uv pip compile --universal --generate-hashes --exclude-newer ...`.
# The --exclude-newer date is the PyPI-snapshot analog of the R image's
# PPM_DATE: it freezes resolution to distributions published on or before that
# date, so the lockfile is reproducible. Edit constraints here, recompile, and
# commit the regenerated requirements.txt.
#
# Version-intent constraints (e.g. numpy>=2.0) belong here; the exact resolved
# version pin lives in requirements.txt.
# =============================================================================

numpy>=2.0
pandas>=2.2
scipy
scikit-learn
pyarrow
polars
matplotlib
seaborn
jupyter
pytest
tomli; python_version < "3.11"   # stdlib's tomllib is 3.11+
